  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Skill Under Sustained Pressure</title>\n<style>\n* {\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n  margin: 0;\n  padding: 0;\n}\n\nbody {\n  font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\n  background: #0a0a0a;\n  color: #e0e0e0;\n  padding: 20px;\n  min-height: 100vh;\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\n}\n\n.container {\n  max-width: 800px;\n  width: 100%;\n}\n\nh1 {\n  font-size: 1.5rem;\n  font-weight: 600;\n  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\n  color: #fff;\n}\n\n.concept {\n  font-size: 0.95rem;\n  line-height: 1.5;\n  color: #999;\n  margin-bottom: 2rem;\n  max-width: 600px;\n}\n\n.teaching-label {\n  font-size: 1rem;\n  color: #fff;\n  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\n  font-weight: 500;\n}\n\n.stage {\n  background: #141414;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  padding: 2rem;\n  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\n}\n\n.controls {\n  display: grid;\n  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));\n  gap: 1.5rem;\n  margin-bottom: 2rem;\n}\n\n.control-group {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  gap: 0.5rem;\n}\n\nlabel {\n  font-size: 0.85rem;\n  color: #aaa;\n  text-transform: uppercase;\n  letter-spacing: 0.5px;\n}\n\nbutton {\n  background: #1a1a1a;\n  border: 1px solid #333;\n  color: #fff;\n  padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;\n  border-radius: 4px;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  font-size: 0.9rem;\n  transition: all 0.2s;\n}\n\nbutton:hover {\n  background: #252525;\n  border-color: #444;\n}\n\nbutton:active {\n  transform: scale(0.98);\n}\n\nbutton.active {\n  background: #2a5aa8;\n  border-color: #3a6ab8;\n}\n\n.canvas-wrapper {\n  position: relative;\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 400px;\n  background: #0a0a0a;\n  border-radius: 4px;\n  overflow: hidden;\n}\n\ncanvas {\n  display: block;\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 100%;\n}\n\n.output {\n  display: grid;\n  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr));\n  gap: 1rem;\n  margin-top: 1.5rem;\n}\n\n.metric {\n  background: #0a0a0a;\n  padding: 1rem;\n  border-radius: 4px;\n  border: 1px solid #222;\n}\n\n.metric-label {\n  font-size: 0.75rem;\n  color: #666;\n  text-transform: uppercase;\n  letter-spacing: 0.5px;\n  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;\n}\n\n.metric-value {\n  font-size: 1.5rem;\n  font-weight: 600;\n  color: #fff;\n}\n\n.metric-value.poor {\n  color: #e85d75;\n}\n\n.metric-value.good {\n  color: #4a9eff;\n}\n\n.explanation {\n  background: #141414;\n  border-left: 3px solid #2a5aa8;\n  padding: 1rem 1.25rem;\n  border-radius: 4px;\n  font-size: 0.9rem;\n  line-height: 1.6;\n  color: #bbb;\n}\n\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n  .controls {\n    grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n  }\n  \n  .canvas-wrapper {\n    height: 300px;\n  }\n}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div class=\"container\">\n  <h1>Skill Under Sustained Pressure</h1>\n  <p class=\"concept\">Elite performance under pressure depends on building decision systems that remain stable when mental fatigue compounds—training the ability to execute the same quality of judgment on the hundredth repetition as on the first, even when stakes are highest.</p>\n  \n  <div class=\"teaching-label\">Watch how decision quality degrades across repeated high-stakes choices as fatigue builds</div>\n  \n  <div class=\"stage\">\n    <div class=\"controls\">\n      <div class=\"control-group\">\n        <label>Training Mode</label>\n        <button id=\"trainingNone\" class=\"training-btn\">No Pressure Practice</button>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"control-group\">\n        <label>&nbsp;</label>\n        <button id=\"trainingPressure\" class=\"training-btn\">Simulated Pressure</button>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"control-group\">\n        <label>Run Sequence</label>\n        <button id=\"runBtn\">Execute 100 Decisions</button>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"canvas-wrapper\">\n      <canvas id=\"canvas\"></canvas>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"output\">\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">Decision 1–25</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-value\" id=\"early\">—</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">Decision 26–50</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-value\" id=\"mid1\">—</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">Decision 51–75</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-value\" id=\"mid2\">—</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">Decision 76–100</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-value\" id=\"late\">—</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"explanation\">\n    <strong>How it works:</strong> Each point represents a high-stakes decision. Without pressure training, quality drops as mental fatigue compounds—by decision 75, you're making choices with the same calculation load but degraded attention. Training under simulated pressure builds systems that hold: pre-decision routines that reset mental state, learned patterns that reduce cognitive load, physical conditioning that delays fatigue onset. The gap between the two curves shows what pressure training builds—not talent, but resilience of decision-making under sustained load.\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\nconst trainingNone = document.getElementById('trainingNone');\nconst trainingPressure = document.getElementById('trainingPressure');\nconst runBtn = document.getElementById('runBtn');\nconst earlyEl = document.getElementById('early');\nconst mid1El = document.getElementById('mid1');\nconst mid2El = document.getElementById('mid2');\nconst lateEl = document.getElementById('late');\n\nlet trainingMode = 'none';\nlet animating = false;\nlet points = [];\n\nfunction resizeCanvas() {\n  const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();\n  canvas.width = rect.width * window.devicePixelRatio;\n  canvas.height = rect.height * window.devicePixelRatio;\n  ctx.scale(window.devicePixelRatio, window.devicePixelRatio);\n  draw();\n}\n\nwindow.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);\nresizeCanvas();\n\ntrainingNone.addEventListener('click', () => {\n  if (animating) return;\n  trainingMode = 'none';\n  trainingNone.classList.add('active');\n  trainingPressure.classList.remove('active');\n  reset();\n});\n\ntrainingPressure.addEventListener('click', () => {\n  if (animating) return;\n  trainingMode = 'pressure';\n  trainingPressure.classList.add('active');\n  trainingNone.classList.remove('active');\n  reset();\n});\n\ntrainingNone.classList.add('active');\n\nrunBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n  if (animating) return;\n  runSequence();\n});\n\nfunction reset() {\n  points = [];\n  earlyEl.textContent = '—';\n  mid1El.textContent = '—';\n  mid2El.textContent = '—';\n  lateEl.textContent = '—';\n  earlyEl.className = 'metric-value';\n  mid1El.className = 'metric-value';\n  mid2El.className = 'metric-value';\n  lateEl.className = 'metric-value';\n  draw();\n}\n\nfunction runSequence() {\n  animating = true;\n  points = [];\n  \n  let hasPosted = false;\n  \n  const numDecisions = 100;\n  let i = 0;\n  \n  const interval = setInterval(() => {\n    if (i >= numDecisions) {\n      clearInterval(interval);\n      animating = false;\n      updateMetrics();\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    const progress = i / numDecisions;\n    let quality;\n    \n    if (trainingMode === 'none') {\n      quality = 0.92 - (progress * 0.35) + (Math.random() * 0.08 - 0.04);\n    } else {\n      quality = 0.90 - (progress * 0.12) + (Math.random() * 0.06 - 0.03);\n    }\n    \n    quality = Math.max(0.4, Math.min(1.0, quality));\n    points.push({ index: i, quality });\n    \n    draw();\n    \n    if (!hasPosted && i > 10) {\n      try {\n        window.parent.postMessage({type: 'interactive_engagement', event: 'manipulated'}, '*');\n      } catch (e) {}\n      hasPosted = true;\n    }\n    \n    i++;\n  }, 20);\n}\n\nfunction updateMetrics() {\n  const early = points.slice(0, 25);\n  const mid1 = points.slice(25, 50);\n  const mid2 = points.slice(50, 75);\n  const late = points.slice(75, 100);\n  \n  const avg = arr => arr.reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.quality, 0) / arr.length;\n  \n  const earlyAvg = avg(early);\n  const mid1Avg = avg(mid1);\n  const mid2Avg = avg(mid2);\n  const lateAvg = avg(late);\n  \n  earlyEl.textContent = (earlyAvg * 100).toFixed(0) + '%';\n  mid1El.textContent = (mid1Avg * 100).toFixed(0) + '%';\n  mid2El.textContent = (mid2Avg * 100).toFixed(0) + '%';\n  lateEl.textContent = (lateAvg * 100).toFixed(0) + '%';\n  \n  earlyEl.className = 'metric-value ' + (earlyAvg >= 0.75 ? 'good' : 'poor');\n  mid1El.className = 'metric-value ' + (mid1Avg >= 0.75 ? 'good' : 'poor');\n  mid2El.className = 'metric-value ' + (mid2Avg >= 0.75 ? 'good' : 'poor');\n  lateEl.className = 'metric-value ' + (lateAvg >= 0.75 ? 'good' : 'poor');\n}\n\nfunction draw() {\n  const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();\n  const w = rect.width;\n  const h = rect.height;\n  \n  ctx.clearRect(0, 0, w, h);\n  \n  ctx.strokeStyle = '#222';\n  ctx.lineWidth = 1;\n  for (let i = 0; i <= 4; i++) {\n    const y = (h / 4) * i;\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.moveTo(0, y);\n    ctx.lineTo(w, y);\n    ctx.stroke();\n  }\n  \n  ctx.fillStyle = '#333';\n  ctx.font = '11px sans-serif';\n  ctx.fillText('100%', 5, 15);\n  ctx.fillText('75%', 5, h / 4 + 5);\n  ctx.fillText('50%', 5, h / 2 + 5);\n  \n  if (points.length === 0) return;\n  \n  ctx.strokeStyle = trainingMode === 'none' ? '#e85d75' : '#4a9eff';\n  ctx.lineWidth = 2;\n  ctx.beginPath();\n  \n  points.forEach((p, idx) => {\n    const x = (p.index / 100) * w;\n    const y = h - (p.quality * h);\n    \n    if (idx === 0) {\n      ctx.moveTo(x, y);\n    } else {\n      ctx.lineTo(x, y);\n    }\n  });\n  \n  ctx.stroke();\n  \n  points.forEach(p => {\n    const x = (p.index / 100) * w;\n    const y = h - (p.quality * h);\n    \n    ctx.fillStyle = trainingMode === 'none' ? '#e85d75' : '#4a9eff';\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.arc(x, y, 2, 0, Math.PI * 2);\n    ctx.fill();\n  });\n}\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
